node.text:
Teresa Baker is building a more inclusive future for the outdoor industry. In this story from @theoutbound, follow her journey as she and a group of diverse outdoor leaders become some of the first members of the public to explore #HaroldRichardsonRedwoodsReserve. It's a massive old-growth redwood grove recently protected by @savetheredwoods in @SonomaCounty.
.
#VisitCalifornia #EveryoneOutside

⚾ Baseball (and occasional fireworks!) at @petcopark. ⁣
⁣
Head to our link in bio for more of Kerry’s ideas on having a perfect #SanDiego day. ⁣
.⁣

node.text:
If you picture yourself sailing off into the sunset like the closing scene of a rom-com, here are a few options for making it happen in real life: ⁣
⁣
⛵️ Book in a lesson at the @sbsailing, which offers a variety of sail and powerboat rentals to help visitors explore the nearby @ChannelIslandsNPS. Or, better yet arrange for a captain to do the steering instead. ⁣
⛵️ Check out @princechartershb for their private cruises onboard a restored classic wooden boat or a vintage yacht in @SurfCityUSA's #HuntingtonHarbor.⁣
⛵️ Set sail in @VisitSanDiego on @svcloudia, a rare restored Norwegian double-ended ketch based on naval designs from the 19th century.⁣
⁣
📷 : @alisandoval1 ⁣
📍: @VisitSantaBarbara⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #SeeSB

node.text:
When it comes to #LosAlamos, all we ask is that you take things slow. Sleep in, have a leisurely brunch, meander to wineries, chill by the pool. The slower pace is what the locals expect of you. ⁣
⁣
You'll find this small town at the north end of the @VisitSYV, about 2.5 hours from @DiscoverLA and an hour from @VisitSantaBarbara. ⁣
⁣
🍽 Eat: @fulloflifefoods for flatbread pizzas baked in a hearth right there in the dining room. ⁣
🍷 Drink: @lofiwine for sipping natural wines while listening to the owner's extensive record collection. ⁣
👀  See: Cruise along Bell Street for some locally-made finds. Start at @sistersgiftsandhome, and stop by @losalamosgallery and @bodegalosalamos to see local art. ⁣
🛌 Stay: at one of the six themed suites at @thevicklosalamos. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @livelikeitsthewknd, @danielmpetersen, @outboundweekend, @afarmedia ⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

Day trips to @VisitLB are always a good idea. Here are four things for an awesome getaway. ⁣
😎 Need more vintage in your wardrobe? Expect awesome independent vintage shops along Retro Row (along 4th Street) ⁣
🎨 Play 'count the murals' along Long Beach's streets (note: you may lose count!) ⁣
🚶🏾‍♀️Keep the walking tour going by checking out the lively coastline, complete with @aquariumpacific, waterfront dining at Shoreline Village and kayaking on Belmont Shore. Oh, and keep an eye out for whales that can be seen year-round. ⁣
🍹 Endless summer nights call for drinks on the patio! Add @mezcalerolbc, @bobeaurooftap or @beachwoodbrewing to the list. ⁣

Let's take a moment to appreciate the trails and facilities that make the outdoors more accessible for everyone. ⁣If you're celebrating #DisabilityPrideMonth and have tips or recommendations based on your own experience, let us know and we'll be sure to pass it on. ⁣
⁣
🌳 Parks including @YosemiteNPS, @sequoiakingsnps, Clear Lake State Park and Montaña de Oro State Park have upgraded some of their trails and campsites to make them wheelchair-accessible. ⁣
🧏🏼‍♀️ @seaworldsandiego can arrange an American sign language interpreter for shows and tours. In addition, @YosemiteNPS and @sequoiakingsnps also offer sign language interpreting and assistive listening devices for park programs. ⁣
🌊 @VisitSanDiego offers free manual or power beach wheelchairs at a number of popular beaches. @SurfCityUSA has rolled out a wheelchair-accessible mat that leads to the water's edge. ⁣
⁣
📷: @wonders_within_reach, @clanhuntington
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia
